### Browser Runtime Environment Detection with Supabase SSR

Source: https://context7.com/supabase/ssr/llms.txt

A utility function `isBrowser()` to reliably detect if the current runtime environment is a web browser. This allows for conditional logic, such as creating the correct Supabase client or safely accessing DOM elements.

```typescript
import { isBrowser } from '@supabase/ssr'

// Conditional client creation based on environment
const createSupabaseClient = () => {
  if (isBrowser()) {
    return createBrowserClient(
      process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL!,
      process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY!
    )
  } else {
    throw new Error('Use createServerClient on the server')
  }
}

// Safe DOM access
if (isBrowser()) {
  document.getElementById('root')?.addEventListener('click', () => {
    console.log('Clicked in browser')
  })
}

// Universal code pattern
const getAuthToken = async () => {
  if (isBrowser()) {
    // Client-side logic
    return localStorage.getItem('auth-token')
  } else {
    // Server-side logic
    const { cookies } = await import('next/headers')
    return cookies().get('auth-token')?.value
  }
}
```
